claim.claim-text:
A method for detecting and measuring CO2 directly in the tissue of a patient by the device or system of claim 1 or 2, the method comprising:
directly contacting the patient's tissue with the probe device;
delivering excitation light to the fluorophor solution within the sensor chamber of the probe;
detecting and measuring fluorescence emitted from the excited fluorophor; and
quantifying tissue CO2 concentration from the measured fluorescence.
